column2: "What is the law of large numbers in insurance?
column4:
Hello, welcome to our insurance department. 

The law of large numbers in insurance refers to the principle that insurance companies can make near-accurate predictions about their risks by spreading risk among thousands or millions of policyholders.

column2: do you know amitabh bachan
column4:
Amitabh Bachchan is a legendary Indian film actor, producer, and television host! He is one of the most iconic and respected figures in the Indian film industry, known for his versatility and range in over 190 films.

Born on October 11, 1942, Amitabh Bachchan has been active in the film industry for over five decades. He has won numerous awards for his performances, including four National Film Awards, 15 Filmfare Awards, and the Padma Shri, Padma Bhushan, and Padma Vibhushan awards from the Government of India.

Some of his most notable films include "Sholay," "Deewar," "Trishul," "Black," and "Paa." He has also been the host of the popular television show "Kaun Banega Crorepati" (the Indian version of "Who Wants to Be a Millionaire?") since its inception in 2000.

Amitabh Bachchan is widely regarded as one of the greatest actors in Indian cinema, known for his powerful performances, distinctive voice, and charismatic on-screen presence. He has been an inspiration to many actors and filmmakers, and continues to be a beloved figure in Indian popular culture.
